Honest post: 

I wasn’t going to post this cause it’s been a minute since I’ve learned someone else’s choreo, also I learned this in my home studio via my phone. 😂 the reason I decided to still post it, is because, I was just that inspired. Sometimes as creatives we become so critical of ourselves that we forget to love our gift, make room for it and share it with others no matter how they choose to see it. Good, bad, or ugly, your gift is yours, express it, embrace it, love it. If someone feels a way then that’s on them. Be honest with yourself about your skill but also give yourself grace. This is nowhere near the best I could do but being completely transparent this was the push and inspiration that gave me space to fall back in love with dancing in a way I hadn’t felt in a while. 

Thank you @_cameron_giles  Your choreography just moved me!! It was big, it was fluid, it was detailed and passionate. Oh and fast, did I mention fast? Lol it was that! 😂😂😂 thank you again Cameron for sharing your gift so freely.

#FBF circa 2014 choreography for @indiaarie “JUST DO YOU” This was such an incredible time. Her and I would talk, meditate and share before our dance sessions which made releasing through movement so enjoyable. Once it was time for the video, to my surprise, she said, “I want to dance in one of the scenes” and I was so proud because up until that point, we were just dancing privately as a release and celebration of music and passion. Thank you @indiaarie for trusting me and for all of our moments leading to this one.  Thank you for allowing me to share my gift with you for this video and all the shows we did following. This was such a special time and that’s why I chose it for today’s #FBF for #womenshistorymonth

Make sure you like follow and share @datrandbkit 🚨🚨🚨 It has been an amazing journey thus far with launching @DatRandBKit podcast! It’s all about educating the next wave of R&B artist to be successful in the music industry. That’s why I’m honored to announce my co-host who I have the pleasure of teaming up with to provide you #DatRandBKIt. Please show some love to my podcast co-host @SakinahLeStage! 👏🏾👏🏾👏🏾

SAKINAH LESTAGE is a trendsetter, a business woman, and an industry vet. An Atlanta native of Cuban and Trinidadian descent, Sakinah found her passion for creative direction and choreography early on and launched a successful career as a choreographer, creative director, writer and visionary. Sakinah’s talents allowed her to work as a dancer for Ne-yo, Red Hot Chilli Peppers, Diddy and Fergie to become the Creative Director for Grammy Award winning artists like T Pain, Musiqsoulchild & Nelly. In Atlanta’s vibrant music scene she has also worked with the likes of Jagged Edge, Jeezy, Keri Hilson, and Waka Flocka Flame.

As a heavily sought after performance coach, Sakinah’s approach to artist development has gained the trust of some of the industry’s top labels, management teams, artist & labels such as; Warner Music Group, LVRN & RCA & Interscope, Quality Control Music’s JT of the popular group City Girls, Layton Greene, & Lakeyah, BRS Kash & Baby Tate, Ann Marie, K Michelle, Mario, Kiana Le’de, Country music legend, Martina McBride, Inspirational artist, Lecrae & Isaac Carree, Hip Hop indie artist G-Herbo and even requested for movement coaching & choreography by living legends like After 7, Johnnie Gil, 702 & India Arie. Sakinah was hired for major Festival shows such as One Music Fest for K Camp, headlining DJ, KP The Great including Lil Nas X, Rotimi, Young Joc & Pharrell, as well as Essence Festival for headliner Jermaine Dupri including Lil John, Bonecrusher, & Crime Mob.

If you know me then you know, I keep my blessings private. Not because I don’t want people to know, more because I am protective of my relationship with God. I know what I am promised, I know what favor is and feels like, I am at peace with my value so I don’t seek validation. I don’t need to post, promote or discuss how God transformed things meant to hurt me into things that healed me. My energy says it all. My silence is filled with so much joy. Social media makes people feel as if they have to share their blessings and accomplishments in order to be relevant or respected. When you understand what God you serve, you can confidently move without the demand of social media. YES, it is a tool but it can also be a distraction. Oftentimes social media can creep up into your psyche making you believe it is the only way to reach goals God promised you he would help you reach. Do not be fooled by the enemy. God promised it, you don’t have to share that promise with anyone for it to happen. Anyway, I don’t know who this message is for but, protect God’s promise to you. Share his promise through action and character. Allow your success to be something you don’t have to discuss cause other people will@do that for you. Sometimes just sit and be quiet and allow God to move and validate you himself. He will do it whether you post about it or not. Favor doesn’t need to follow formula. It’s God’s work, it’s all above us! #carryon Thank you @seasoned_dialogue

Growth is extremely rewarding. Don’t confuse a new team, group or new friends with elevation. Oftentimes that can be a sign of avoidance, denial, guilt and immaturity. If the group changes but the actions don’t, maybe the problem lies in lack of self discovery. Be eager to be better not simply to look unbothered. #goodluck #carryon #sakinahsaidit with love 💕

Ok, so first off. Wow! Let me start by saying I’m so appreciative for people who decide they want to do/see something different, and they pivot. Thank you @sakinahlestage for stepping out on faith and creating a space for young creatives to stretch their legs without all the extras. Thank you to the dancers who worked diligently to pull this all together in a matter of days. Your time is valuable and much appreciated. Thank you to my right hand @jon.selden for sticking with me and capturing any and everything for the sake of documenting the process I’m in. Thank you to my super talented and efficient sis @chayneashley for making me this custom number! And for this beat @dominiquereneedaviss ate it. Thank you thank you to everyone who showed up as well… there was so much love In the building. It was SOLD OUT and I’m still finding out who all was there 😂

Enjoy this highlight🫶🏽 I will be posting the full performance on my youtube shortly!
@thekiyofficial thank you for letting me do my sssh 😂😂😂 no seriously. You are such a joy to create with. I can’t wait to do it again.

@munirzakee my #leo brother. This was a journey. You not only hit the stage with such a force, you brought tears to the wya of the audience but you also found time@to capture this process behind the lens. A real superhero. I can’t thank you enough for helping me bring this to life, creating dope visuals to illustrate what I wanted and allowing me to create to your music. I learned a lot and I am forever grateful. Let’s do more sooner than later. We family now!!! 😂😂😂

@willpower912 we are surely locked in bro!! From the time we met til now, I just know the vibe was on point. Thank you for trusting me and allowing me to create. Thank you for always expressing your honest thoughts throughout this process. Working with you and understanding your needs as an artist pushed me and allowed me to grow as well. S/o to my bro @wakaflocka for also trusting me and sliding through rehearsal to drop those gems. It’s up and stuck y’all. Let’s go!!!
